name: NearMiss - Testing The Ends Of What They'll Put Up With
description: 01. Serious Mess 02. Call For Help 03. Now Rectify 04. Falling Out 05. Take It Back 06. In A Daydream 07. Feel When You Find 08. Last Goodnight 09. The Choice 10. At One Place 11. We All Bleed 12. You’ve Mistaken The sophomore release from one of Austin, TX’s premier punk bands. Don’t let the members’ ex-Bigwig status fool you; Testing The Ends Of What They’ll Put Up With is distinctively NearMiss. With edgy vocals, crunchy guitar riffs and amazing punk rock drumming, Testing The Ends… is a must-have for any punker’s CD collection.

name: Strike Fire Fall - Still Life
description: 01. Cadillac 02. Flying Blind 03. Freud Said It Was Cool 04. Promises Of Real Life 05. Verona Post 06. Stay Awake 07. Ken 08. Awkward Pose 09. Music And Spirits 10. Canned Laughter 11. U-Turn 12. Aquafolium 13. Say Hello 14. Aces Over Eights With attention to melody and detail as the band’s primary focus, Strike Fire Fall found themselves being voted the winners of the 2004 “Sign My Band” contest out of over 7,000 entries. Their debut LP, Still Life, was recorded by Jason Yan (The Matches, Paramore, Yellowcard) and boasts 14 tracks of upbeat, catchy rock music that will get stuck in your head for days.

Warren’s Song Pt. 22 17. Warren’s Song Pt. 13 The long-awaited LP produced, recorded and mixed by Bracket! This former Fat Wreck Chords band proves they still got it with Requiem, their first studio release in six years. The 17-song masterpiece features vocals harmonies that rival those of the Beach Boys, layered over the classic power-pop-punk sound Bracket has become know for.
